Year = {2024},
Volume = {55},
Month = {AUG},
Abstract = {The dataset consists of records from the NTFS file system and event
   logs. In this study, we used images of devices from capture the flags
   competitions focused on the digital forensic of Windows operating
   systems and user activities. We created timelines of the security
   incident from the disk images using the Plaso tool, which we then
   processed and transformed the attributes of the timelines into binary
   values to simplify the application of data analysis and machine learning
   methods. The data are divided into 12 different files, and they are
   saved in CSV format. (c) 2024 The Authors. Published by Elsevier Inc.
