Month = {JUL-DEC},
Abstract = {In this research, the theory of incivilities is tested to explain the
   formation of burglary hotspots in the Metropolitan Area of Queretaro.
   The data was obtained from an own survey and a web scraping application
   for the construction of spatial data. The relationship between the
   variables is investigated using a Poisson point process that attempts to
   explain the intensity of the phenomenon in a region. The results show
   that the price of housing maintains a negative relationship with the
   intensity of house robberies; Regarding incivilities, only graffiti and
   lawn maintenance matter.},
