Month = {JUL},
Abstract = {Information forensics and security (IFS) is an active R \& D area whose
   goal is to ensure that people use devices, data, and intellectual
   properties for authorized purposes and to facilitate the gathering of
   solid evidence to hold perpetrators accountable. For over a quarter
   century, since the 1990s, the IFS research area has grown tremendously
   to address the societal needs of the digital information era. The IEEE
   Signal Processing Society (SPS) has emerged as an important hub and
   leader in this area, and this article celebrates some landmark technical
   contributions. In particular, we highlight the major technological
   advances by the research community in some selected focus areas in the
   field during the past 25 years and present future trends.},
