Abstract = {A hyperspectral image makes it possible to collect and process
   information in the electromagnetic spectrum. Through the analysis of
   these images, information on the chemical composition of the sample
   under study can be obtained. The field of application of this type of
   technology is very extensive: the food industry, pharmaceuticals,
   forensic analysis or the field of restoration are just some of the most
   widespread examples. This article presents the work-in-progress to
   obtain a low-cost and portable hyperspectral imaging camera, so that it
   can be used in the fields of application mentioned above, as well as in
   certain subjects such as computer image analysis, machine learning, etc.
   The camera designed and tested in the first prototype is based on the
   use of several low-cost embedded systems and simple electronics and
   mechanics, so that it is an easily replicable DIY solution.},
