Abstract = {Probabilistic relational databases (PDB) have extended from the
   relational database model by incorporating probability measures to
   capture the data uncertainty associated with data items. There are many
   useful applications have been studied such as consolidation the results
   of market surveys for many major industries; improving internet
   comparison shopping; consolidating crime-fighting information from
   different witnesses. In BioCom'08, we have applied the probabilistic
   relational database techniques to the area of biomedical informatics. In
   this paper, we further present a software system development for
   probabilistic relational database web-based applications and services.
   Our discussions are focused on more biomedical informatics applications
   such as disease analysis, control and prevention; data mining and
